    {
      "textBlocks": [
        {
          "body": "The werebear can use its action to polymorph into a Large bear-humanoid hybrid or into a Large bear, or back into its true form, which is humanoid. Its statistics, other than its size and AC, are the same in each form. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying isn't transformed. It reverts to its true form if it dies.",
          "title": "Shapechanger"
        },
        {
          "body": "The werebear has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell.",
          "title": "Keen Smell"
        },
        {
          "body": "In bear form, the werebear makes two claw attacks. In humanoid form, it makes two greataxe attacks. In hybrid form, it can attack like a bear or a humanoid.",
          "title": "Multiattack"
        },
        {
          "body": "The statistics presented in this section assume a base creature of human. However, you can also use the statistics to represent nonhuman lycanthropes, adding verisimilitude by allowing a nonhuman lycanthrope to retain one or more of its humanoid racial traits. For example, an elf werewolf might have the Fey Ancestry trait.",
          "title": "Variant: Nonhuman Lycanthropes "
        }
      ],
      "title": "Abilities"
    }
